    {
      "id": "1ae4750c-f3ba-80d0-b708-c4d2f8beefd5",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In MOOCs, learners are often requested to perform peer-reviews. However, the peer-review process is often innacurate. The study uses a Transformer-based Language Model (a fine-tuned Distillbert) to do essay-scoring. The authors find that using this approach generates more reliable results than standard peer-review by learners. ",
